06, \"to\": 1611}, {\"ngram\": \"the table\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1648}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Catholic leaders from around the world, including the French bishops conference and two Vatican officials, condemned the performance, with at least one, Archbishop Charles Scicluna of Malta and adjunct secretary of the Vatican's Dicastery for the Doctrine of the Faith, making a formal complaint to the French ambassador to Malta, encouraging others to do the same.\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1651, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.855129898514226e-12, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1705, \"end\": 1711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999993153867378, \"rank\": 6.84323859019513e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.8216298681008182, \"rank\": 0.13985046802135578, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1815, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charles Scicluna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\"}, {\"begin\": 1835, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9999999974647835, \"rank\": 2.5265576427007346e-09, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \